{
  "texts": [
    "This rarely happens but should be properly handled when happening.",
    "Therefore, if the fraction of valid SMILES strings (out of the 128 sampled in each episode) is less than 0.8 for more than 10 consecutive episodes, the parameters of the algorithm will be reset to that of the pre-trained model.",
    "Table 2 in Appendix A displays a list of hyperparameters and the values employed in this paper.",
    "Advantage Actor-Critic (A2C) is a synchronous version of the A3C algorithm (Mnih et al., 2016), wherein the following definition of the advantage is used where V (s t) is the value network with (non-shared) parameters and discount factor.",
    "We adapt A2C to the setting where the state vectors are represented by the RNN outputs of the latest recurrent node."
